7¶U<?php exit; ?>a:1:{s:7:"content";s:1778:"Trevor is highly skilled in the successful treatment of: generalised anxiety, panic attacks, social anxiety, post-traumatic stress disorder, health anxiety, obsessive compulsive disorder, low mood and depression (including bipolar disorder) anger difficulties, poor self-esteem, lack of confidence, addictions, stress-related illnesses, chronic pain, eating disorders, adjustment to injury and work related stress.</p>

<p>He graduated with an Honours degree in Psychology from the University of Hull in 1985 (receiving a prize for his final year studies) before being awarded a postgraduate scholarship to study at Edinburgh University. He graduated from Edinburgh University in 1990 with a Masters Degree in Clinical Psychology.</p>

<p>Further studies have included: (i) clinical hypnosis at Sheffield University (ii) cognitive therapy at the nationally renowned Newcastle Cognitive Therapy Centre, for which he was awarded their post graduate diploma and (iii) the receiving of a Doctorate in Clinical Psychology from Cardiff University in 2001, for his pioneering work in the field of mindfulness training.</p>

<p>Trevor's professional memberships and registrations include: Member of the Australian Psychological Society (APS), Member of the APSâ€™s College of Clinical Psychologists, Registered with the Psychology Board of Australia, Approved Supervisor with the Psychology Board of Australia, Registered Medicare Specialist Clinical Psychology Provider, Associate Fellow of the British Psychological Society, UK Chartered Clinical Psychologist, Accredited Cognitive Behavioural Psychotherapist with the British Association of Behavioural and Cognitive Psychotherapy, Member of The British Society of Clinical and Academic Hypnosis and UK Chartered Scientist.</p>";}